<Defs>




<!-- GAME STARTUP -->

<!-- 1. Launch successful -->
<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionGameStartPopup1</defName>
	<title>Launch successful!</title>
	<description>
&lt;color=#8ECbFF&gt;&lt;b&gt;Welcome to the Progression Modpack!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/color&gt;
\n
&lt;size=25&gt;&lt;b&gt;Ready to start!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
\n
You made it, the modpack has booted successfully. Thanks for sticking through the loading process. If you're seeing this popup, everything is now fully initialized and ready. Click next to learn some integral aspects of the modpack.
\n\n
This series of messages will only appear on your first launch. If you&#39;d ever like to view them again, you can reset your popup knowledge in the &lt;b&gt;Popup Framework&lt;/b&gt; mod options.
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/ProgressionLogo</iconPath>
	<imageRatio>0.4</imageRatio>
	<dimensions>(988, 620)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Center</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>true</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<nextPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup2</nextPopupDef>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<trigger>OnGameStartup</trigger>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>


<!-- 2. Loading times -->
<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionGameStartPopup2</defName>
	<title>Loading times</title>
	<description>
&lt;b&gt;About startup time&lt;/b&gt;
\n
&lt;size=18&gt;Don't be alarmed. Depending on your system, startup load times can range from roughly &lt;b&gt;7 to 50 minutes&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
Most players on mid-range hardware should expect something closer to &lt;b&gt;20–25 minutes&lt;/b&gt;. This is normal, and will occur every time you launch the game.
The speed of loading is based primarily on single-core CPU performance and SSD speeds.
\n
Ensure RimWorld and its Workshop content are installed on an SSD. If long load times are an issue, upgrading your CPU (single-core speed) will have the biggest impact.
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/LoadingScreen</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(988, 620)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>false</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<previousPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup1</previousPopupDef>
	<nextPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup3</nextPopupDef>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<trigger>None</trigger>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>


<!-- 3. Outdated mods -->
<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionGameStartPopup3</defName>
	<title>Mods reporting "outdated"</title>
	<description>
&lt;b&gt;About &quot;outdated&quot; mod warnings&lt;/b&gt;
\n
&lt;size=18&gt;Some mods may show as being for older RimWorld versions. This is &lt;b&gt;normal&lt;/b&gt; and usually just means the author hasn&#39;t updated the mod&#39;s metadata.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
Many of these are simple retextures or XML-only changes, which often continue working fine across versions without needing an update.
\n
If it looks a little scary, don&#39;t worry. This modpack is curated for a stable, high-quality experience, even when a mod&#39;s metadata hasn&#39;t caught up.
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/OutdatedMods</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(988, 620)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>false</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<previousPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup2</previousPopupDef>
	<nextPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup4</nextPopupDef>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<trigger>None</trigger>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>


<!-- 4. Updating the modpack -->
<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionGameStartPopup4</defName>
	<title>Updating the modpack</title>
	<description>
&lt;b&gt;A word on modpack updates&lt;/b&gt;
\n
&lt;size=18&gt;The modpack does not update automatically. Updates can be applied manually using the same steps you followed during installation.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
An easier option is to follow the &lt;b&gt;#pack-updates&lt;/b&gt; channel on Discord and choose which updates you&#39;d like to apply at your own discretion.
\n
When updating mid-save, there is one important rule to understand: &lt;b&gt;adding mods is usually safe&lt;/b&gt;, but &lt;b&gt;removing mods mid-save is very likely to break your save&lt;/b&gt;.
If you plan to update an existing save, it&#39;s strongly recommended that you only add mods. Save-breaking removals should be reserved for starting a new colony.
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/Updating</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(988, 620)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>false</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<previousPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup3</previousPopupDef>
	<nextPopupDef>ProgressionGameStartPopup5</nextPopupDef>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<trigger>None</trigger>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>


