<!-- 'NEW COLONY' BUTTON -->
<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionNewColony</defName>
	<title>Starting technology</title>
	<description>
&lt;size=22&gt;&lt;b&gt;Choosing your start&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
\n\n
&lt;size=15&gt;You&#39;re about to select a scenario for a new colony. Your first major decision is your &lt;b&gt;starting technology&lt;/b&gt; — the tech level your journey begins in.&lt;/size&gt;
\n\n
&lt;size=15&gt;If you&#39;re prone to &lt;b&gt;choice paralysis&lt;/b&gt;, starting in the &lt;b&gt;Animal / Neolithic&lt;/b&gt; era is highly recommended. Fewer systems, fewer decisions, and a smoother ramp into the modpack.&lt;/size&gt;
\n\n
&lt;size=15&gt;If you want access to many options immediately and enjoy juggling complexity, feel free to start in the &lt;b&gt;Medieval&lt;/b&gt; era or beyond.&lt;/size&gt;
\n\n
&lt;size=16&gt;&lt;b&gt;Once you're in-game, you can progress upward through the tech eras and see them all. There&#39;s no wrong choice, and you can always start fresh whenever you'd like.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/TechLevels</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(980, 620)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>false</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<trigger>OnNewColonyButton</trigger>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
	<nextPopupDef>ProgressionDifficultyCommitment</nextPopupDef>
	<!-- <imageRatio>0.7</imageRatio> -->
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>

<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionDifficultyCommitment</defName>
	<title>Difficulty and commitment mode</title>
	<description>
&lt;size=22&gt;&lt;b&gt;This is a baseline challenging experience.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
\n
&lt;size=15&gt;Higher difficulty settings often encourage &lt;b&gt;degenerative or exploitative playstyles&lt;/b&gt;, such as killboxing or wealth exploits especially in a modpack of this scale and complexity.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
&lt;size=15&gt;If your goal is to focus on &lt;b&gt;narrative, experimentation, and the systems of the modpack&lt;/b&gt;, consider playing on an &lt;b&gt;easier difficulty&lt;/b&gt; than you might normally choose.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
&lt;size=22&gt;&lt;b&gt;Recommended save setting&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
&lt;size=15&gt;Playing with &lt;b&gt;'Reload anytime mode'&lt;/b&gt; is strongly recommended. With 1000+ mods, occasional updates or edge cases can destabilize saves, and having the ability to reload acts as a practical safety net.&lt;/size&gt;
&lt;size=15&gt;If you prefer the tension of not reloading out of bad situations, that experience can still exist, it just relies on &lt;b&gt;self-imposed narrative discipline&lt;/b&gt; rather than enforced restrictions.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
&lt;size=16&gt;&lt;b&gt;Choose the settings that support the story you want to tell.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/Difficulty</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(980, 620)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>true</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
	<previousPopupDef>ProgressionNewColony</previousPopupDef>
	<trigger>None</trigger>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>







<!-- COLONY START -->


	<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
		<defName>ProgressionColonyStartPopup1</defName>
		<title>Note on intended playstyle</title>
		<description>
&lt;b&gt;Note: This is an experience about narrative.&lt;/b&gt;
While there is no wrong way to play RimWorld, this modpack is &lt;i&gt;not&lt;/i&gt; designed around min-max or optimizing play. It isn&#39;t something to be conquered, it&#39;s meant to be used as a tool for narrative exploration.
\nThere is no single &quot;best way&quot; to do anything here. There are simply too many paths, systems, and outcomes for that to exist.
Go with what feels right to you, and to the story you&#39;re trying to tell.
		</description>
		<iconPath>Tutor/Narrative</iconPath>
		<dimensions>(700, 450)</dimensions>
		<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
		<!-- <customButtonLabel>Get help</customButtonLabel>
		<customButtonWebLink>https://discord.gg/b58NcrzxRS</customButtonWebLink> -->
		<closeable>false</closeable>
		<oneTime>true</oneTime>
		<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
		<nextPopupDef>ProgressionColonyStarDifficultyStorytellers</nextPopupDef>
		<!-- <nextPopupDef>ProgressionColonyStartPopup3</nextPopupDef> -->
		<trigger>OnColonyStartup</trigger>
		<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
	</PopupFramework.PopupDef>

<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionColonyStarDifficultyStorytellers</defName>
	<title>Changing aspects mid-game</title>
	<description>
&lt;size=18&gt;&lt;b&gt;Change difficulty or storyteller anytime&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
&lt;size=14&gt;If the game ever feels like it&#39;s pulling you out of the moment, whether due to difficulty or the storyteller you chose, you can freely change both &lt;b&gt;mid-game&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/size&gt;
\n\n
&lt;size=14&gt;To do this, open &lt;b&gt;Options&lt;/b&gt;, go to &lt;b&gt;Gameplay&lt;/b&gt;, and click &lt;b&gt;Modify&lt;/b&gt; on the storyteller settings. From there, you can adjust difficulty, storyteller behavior, or swap storytellers entirely.&lt;/size&gt;
\n
&lt;size=16&gt;&lt;b&gt;Set it to whatever keeps you in sync with the game.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/Storyteller</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(700, 450)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<closeable>false</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<previousPopupDef>ProgressionColonyStartPopup1</previousPopupDef>
	<nextPopupDef>ProgressionColonyStartEnd</nextPopupDef>
	<trigger>OnColonyStartup</trigger>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>

<PopupFramework.PopupDef>
	<defName>ProgressionColonyStartEnd</defName>
	<title>Enjoy the game.</title>
	<description>
&lt;size=18&gt;&lt;b&gt;You&#39;re good to go.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/size&gt;
\n
The project is designed to feel cohesive and intentional, but feedback plays a huge role in how it continues to improve.
If you have any questions, bug reports, or general feedback (even something as small as a typo) please don&#39;t hesitate to share it.
There&#39;s a large, friendly community ready to help. Ask anything, anytime.
Enjoy your story, and come tell us about it afterward!
	</description>
	<iconPath>Tutor/ProgressionLogo</iconPath>
	<dimensions>(700, 450)</dimensions>
	<orientationStyle>Right</orientationStyle>
	<customButtonLabel>Join the discord</customButtonLabel>
	<customButtonWebLink>https://discord.gg/b58NcrzxRS</customButtonWebLink>
	<closeable>true</closeable>
	<oneTime>true</oneTime>
	<saveToClient>true</saveToClient>
	<previousPopupDef>ProgressionColonyStarDifficultyStorytellers</previousPopupDef>
	<sound>ProgressionPopup</sound>
</PopupFramework.PopupDef>
